  "model": "automatic",
  "whatsapp_greeting": "Hey coach, I'm your Playmaker assistant from LocalLane. I know your playbook, your roster, and your game day plans. Want a readiness check, play info, or help planning practice?",
  "memory_config": {
    "enabled": true,
    "scope": "both",
    "instructions": "Save global memories for: team patterns (which plays are run most, common formations, typical game day play count), quiz trends (which plays are hardest for the team, where most mistakes happen), seasonal rhythms (practice days, game schedule, league structure), and platform feature updates that affect the workspace.\n\nSave per-user memories for: each player's learning style (do they study in bursts or steady, do they quiz themselves or need prompting), position and role on the team, mastery patterns (which play types they excel at, which they struggle with), streaks and milestones worth celebrating, and how coaches like to plan (detailed or big picture, how far ahead they prepare).\n\nWhen to save: After learning something that would help you support this person better next time. When a coach shares their coaching philosophy. When a player's learning pattern becomes clear. When someone corrects you. When a milestone is reached (first quiz, first streak of 10, all plays mastered).\n\nWhat NOT to save: One-time questions, temporary debugging, anything a user asks you to forget."
  },
  "name": "PlaymakerAgent"
}